Downbender bundles the following third-party software inside its application bundle:

- yt-dlp (https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp)
  Released into the public domain under The Unlicense.

- FFmpeg: ffmpeg and ffprobe (https://ffmpeg.org)
  GPL-licensed macOS arm64 builds from https://ffmpeg.martin-riedl.de,
  which publishes the build configuration and corresponding sources for
  each build. FFmpeg source code is available at https://ffmpeg.org.
  Because these builds are GPL, Downbender as a whole is distributed
  under the GNU General Public License v3 (see LICENSE).

- Deno (https://deno.com)
  MIT License. Bundled as the JavaScript runtime yt-dlp uses to solve
  YouTube's EJS challenges.

None of these binaries are stored in this repository; scripts/fetch-binaries.sh
downloads them at build time from the sources above.
